  "prompt": "College and NCAA Football: (NFL) In overtime, is the kicking team allowed to do an onside kick and if successful does the other team get the ball afterwards?",
  "response": "In the NFL, during overtime, the kicking team is allowed to attempt an onside kick. If the kicking team successfully recovers the onside kick, they retain possession of the ball and can continue their drive. The opposing team does not automatically get the ball after an onside kick recovery.\n\nHowever, if the kicking team fails to recover the onside kick and the receiving team successfully recovers it, the receiving team takes possession at the spot where they recovered the kick. So, in summary, if the kicking team recovers the onside kick, they keep the ball; if the receiving team recovers it, they take possession.",
